  "type": "spr",
  "stem": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">If <math alttext=\"six sevenths p plus 18 equals 54\"><mfrac>\n\t<mn>6</mn>\n\t<mn>7</mn>\n</mfrac>\n<mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>18</mn>\n<mo>=</mo><mn>54</mn>\n</math>, what is the value of <math alttext=\"7 p\"><mrow>\n\t<mn>7</mn>\n\t<mi>p</mi>\n</mrow>\n</math>?</p>",
  "answerOptions": null,
  "keys": [
    "294"
  ],
  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The correct answer is <math alttext=\"294\"><mn>294</mn>\n</math>. Subtracting <math alttext=\"18\"><mn>18</mn>\n</math> from each side of the given equation yields <math alttext=\"six sevenths p equals 36\"><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>7</mn></mfrac><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>36</mn></math>. Multiplying each side of this equation by <math alttext=\"seven sixths\"><mfrac>\n<mn>7</mn>\n<mn>6</mn>\n</mfrac>\n</math> yields <math alttext=\"p equals 42\"><mrow>\n<mi>p</mi>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mn>42</mn>\n</mrow>\n</math>. Multiplying each side of this equation by <math alttext=\"7\"><mn>7</mn>\n</math> yields <math alttext=\"7 p equals 294\"><mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mn>7</mn>\n<mi>p</mi>\n</mrow>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mn>294</mn>\n</mrow>\n</math>. Therefore, the value of <math alttext=\"7 p\"><mrow>\n<mn>7</mn>\n<mi>p</mi>\n</mrow>\n</math> is <math alttext=\"294\"><mn>294</mn>\n</math>.</p>",
